[h3 id=NoteToPublicationTeam 
	"Note to Publication Team
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"I don't know well enough (and can'f figure it out with a quick search) if there are any differences between the languages other than simply language timing to warrant splitting the regions into separate publications (i.e. having all 4 potential options: "any %" and "hero only" of both Japanese and English).  All I know is that speedrun.com splits them; that may simply be due to the significant difference in language timing in regards to a leaderboard setup.  I'm guessing RNG would be impacted by the timing differences even if ther isn't anything else.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"As-is, this run doesn't compete with the current publication.  But if someone were to submit an any % Japanese run (or an English "hero only" run), the judge--
	[small 
		"I hope it's not me
	]small
	"--would have to sort through a 
	[b 
		[em 
			"massive 
		]em
	]b
	" amount of text and gameplay to definitively say one run was better than the other from a only-gameplay-improvement standpoint.  So this may be a situation where splitting languages is warranted even if the actual gameplay is otherwise identical or very similar (which I wouldn't expect due to the above mentioned expected changes in RNG).  I'll leave the ultimate decision on whether or not this suggested splitting should happen up to the senior Judge and Publisher.
	$LF
